news.title: Ahmedabad civic body announces new rules for ready-mix concrete plants
news.para: The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation has mandated permits for all ready-mix concrete (RMC) plants, both on-site and off-site, operating within city limits. Commercial RMC plants are now restricted to industrial, agricultural, and logistical zones, while on-site plants are limited to construction sites. This decision, made to combat air pollution, requires plants to relocate from residential areas and obtain necessary clearances.

news.title: Telangana government eyes over ₹2,000 crore per acre in Raidurg land auction
news.para: Telangana government plans to auction two land parcels in Raidurg Knowledge City. The auction aims to generate over Rs 2,000 crore. The base price is set at Rs 101 crore per acre. The e-auction is scheduled for October 6. The location is near major companies and has good connectivity. Successful bidders must pay within 90 days.

news.title: Can’t deny housing society membership to homebuyers over builder’s default: HC
news.para: The Bombay High Court has ruled that a housing society cannot deny membership to flat purchasers based on a developer's non-compliance with the development agreement. Justice Amit Borkar directed a Vile Parle society to grant membership to 17 flat purchasers, emphasizing that membership eligibility is determined by cooperative society laws, rules, and bye-laws, not external contracts.

news.title: Stuck for 20 years, new firm may take over mall plot in Ghaziabad
news.para: Ghaziabad Development Authority is poised to transfer a 46,000sqm plot near Shaheed Sthal New Bus Adda metro station to Sakshi Fincap Private Ltd, after the initial developer, Celebration City, defaulted on payments for a mall project two decades ago.

news.title: BlackRock inks 1.43 lakh office lease with IndiQube in Bengaluru
news.para: BlackRock Services India has inked a 10-year lease for 143,000 sq ft at IndiQube Symphony in Bengaluru's CBD, valued at Rs 410 crore. This significant deal underscores the area's appeal for global capability centers. IndiQube, following its IPO, is expanding its managed workspace, capitalizing on the rising demand for flexible office solutions in India.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to launch sealing drive against property tax defaulters
news.para: The Municipal Corporation of Gurugram (MCG) is set to initiate a sealing drive targeting 65 property owners, primarily commercial and industrial units, who each have outstanding property tax dues exceeding Rs 1 crore.

news.title: DTCP suspends project licence, orders FIR against directors of company
news.para: Gurugram's DTCP suspended Prime Time Infraproject's license for its residential colony in Pataudi Sector 1 due to persistent defaults and violation of agreements. Authorities halted registrations, sealed the site, and ordered an FIR against the directors. This action aims to protect consumer interests and enforce development norms, sending a strong message to non-compliant developers.

news.title: Government nod to set up Infopark’s phase III campus in 300 acres
news.para: Kochi's IT sector is set for a major expansion as the state government has granted in-principle approval for Infopark Phase III, spanning over 300 acres in Kunnathunadu. This IT-integrated township will include residential, commercial, sports, and medical facilities.

news.title: Protest over Ambuja Cements plant in Kalyan grows, hearing on September 16
news.para: Residents of Ambivli and surrounding villages are protesting a proposed Rs 1,400-crore cement plant by Ambuja Cements, an Adani Group subsidiary, citing health and environmental concerns. The plant's proximity to residential areas and rivers violates environmental norms, sparking widespread opposition. Villagers claim the project contradicts earlier promises of a local warehouse and job creation.

news.title: Kolkata civic body makes visitor car parks must in residential projects over 53,000 sq ft
news.para: Kolkata Municipal Corporation (KMC) has mandated visitor parking in residential projects exceeding 5,000 sq m, offering additional FAR for developers to build these spaces. At least 25% of the additional FAR must be reserved for visitors' car park.

news.title: Buyers await Uttar Pradesh RERA action on stalled project
news.para: The Palacio Imperial White Buyers Association, after filing a complaint in June 2025, is still awaiting a hearing from Uttar Pradesh RERA regarding the stalled Palacio Imperial White project. The association seeks handover of the project from Tulsiani Infraventure, now Pure Earth Terrawise Builtech, due to prolonged delays, raising concerns about regulatory inaction and potential financial losses for homebuyers.

news.title: Amaravati JAC leader appointed as Andhra Pradesh-RERA chairman
news.para: Amaravati JAC leader A Siva Reddy has been appointed as the chairman of Andhra Pradesh Real Estate Regulatory Authority (AP-RERA). He aims to ensure transparency and efficiency in the real estate sector, protect consumer interests, and establish a speedy dispute redressal mechanism. AP-RERA will regulate both residential and commercial real estate transactions, ensuring developers provide comprehensive project information to consumers.

news.title: Raheja Universal buys back headquarter for ₹211 crore
news.para: Raheja Universal has reacquired its former corporate headquarters, Raheja Centre-Point, for ₹211 crore. The five-story commercial building, originally developed by Raheja Universal in 2004, was sold to HDFC in 2020 as part of a portfolio realignment. Following HDFC's merger with HDFC Bank, Raheja Universal successfully bid to buy back the property.

news.title: New Zealand home prices dip in August, buyers remain cautious
news.para: New Zealand's housing market experienced a slight dip in August, with median home prices decreasing by 1.3% from July and 0.5% year-on-year, according to REINZ. Despite aggressive interest rate cuts by the Reserve Bank of New Zealand to stimulate the economy, prospective buyers remain cautious. Seasonally adjusted national home sales also fell 4.5% from July, although they were up 0.

news.title: China's home prices extend decline, more policy support needed
news.para: China's housing market continues its decline, with new home prices falling again in August, extending a slump since May 2023. Despite stimulus measures, the sector remains a drag on economic growth. Analysts anticipate further adjustments and call for stronger measures to stabilize the market, including easing restrictions and potential interest rate cuts, as weak demand and economic headwinds persist.

news.title: Delhi civic body launches user-friendly property tax calculator for easy self-assessment
news.para: The Municipal Corporation of Delhi has launched a property tax calculator. Citizens can now calculate their tax independently. The tool is available on the official portal. Users can download a PDF of the calculation. A helpdesk is also available on the website. The 'Suniyo' scheme has generated over Rs 304 crore.

news.title: Signature View residents vacate flats as DDA offers monthly rent aid ahead of demolition
news.para: Following IIT Delhi's assessment deeming Signature View apartments structurally unsafe, the DDA has initiated demolition proceedings. Residents are gradually vacating the premises, aided by monthly rent assistance of Rs 50,000 for three-bedroom and Rs 38,000 for two-bedroom flats.

news.title: Birla Corporation to consolidate operations in cement business
news.para: Birla Corporation Limited, a key player in central India's cement industry with a 20 million tonne capacity, aims to expand to 27.6 million tonnes by 2028-29 with a Rs 4335 crore investment. The company is also exploring diversification opportunities and focusing on its jute business, while increasing its renewable energy consumption to protect its market share and enhance value.

news.title: House prices in UK fall while rents rise by least in four years: Surveys
news.para: Britain's housing market is showing signs of cooling as asking prices for homes dipped 0.1% annually in September, the first decline since January. Rightmove data indicates southern England properties are primarily driving this decrease. Simultaneously, Zoopla reports that average rental price increases have slowed to a four-year low of 2.4%, with monthly rents averaging £1,300.

news.title: Bhopal metro gains ground as it looks to acquire land by consent or via SDM
news.para: Landowners along Bhopal Metro's Orange Line are increasingly embracing the Mutual Purchase Policy, expediting land acquisition through mutual consent and compensation within two months. Forty property owners have already agreed, with compensation for structures and full payment for landowners.
